<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Air</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Levitate<br>
See Invis<br>
10/15/25 to all resists.<br>
<br>
Sounds good right? Sure if you ignore a couple little facts:<br>
1)Several of the zones where this would be considered desirable have levitate disabled. Can't use this in such places.<br>
2)The resists will only last until your first death/LD/zone and then they are gone.... Remember that 72 min reuse, and even if you don't die/LD/zone you lose it after 36 mins (more if you are wearing an Ext. Enh. item) and are without the resists for a minimum for 36 aditional minutes (less if you use an EE item).<br>
3)Illusions use a buff-slot. This is (primarily) a raid situation ability. Buff slots tend to be in short supply on raids, even with the addition of the bardsong box.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Earth</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
+ 10/15/20 STA<br>
+ 50/100/200 HP (both curent and max)<br>
<br>
At least this doesn't have the levitate to disable it in several places. The extra HP might even save your life.<br>
Keep in mind that you can only have it up 50% of the time. Also, the situations where this is of the most potential use are raid situations and you have that potential problem of buff slots. This is, in my opinion, the one where the benefits come closest to justifying the cost but it stil doesn't make it there.<br>
<br>
At 60, factoring in the STA (and assuming your STA doesn't hit or exceed 255), the actual HP gains are : 74/136/248.<br>
<br>
That is 24.67 / 15.11 / 13.78 HP/AA point spent.<br>
<br>
Compare that to Natural Durability. Using a naked level 60 Mage with 80 STA as a lowball example, the base HP on which ND will work is 917 (based on the formulas used at Magelo).<br>
<br>
ND will then give 18 / 45 / 92 HP when naked. <br>
Every HP or point of STA on your equipment will increase that.<br>
<br>
Just going by naked values you get 9 / 7.5 / 7.66 HP/AA spent with ND. These numbers are smaller than the Earth form numbers, but they aren't factoring in your equipment.<br>
<br>
With my current equpment/level/stats (see magelo ling in sig), I have an unbuffed HP of 1561. For me ND would give 31 / 78 / 156 HP. That works out to  15.5 / 13 / 13 HP/AA. Much closer to the Earth values and as my equipment improves the benefit I would gain from ND increases - unlike Earth which will remain a constant or even decrease (if I chose to load up on STA producing items/AAs) though that isn't likely. Also, I would get the ND benefits full time.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Fire</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
10/20/30 point DS<br>
+10/15/20 INT<br>
+1/3/5 to effective casting level<br>
<br>
DS : if you are geting beat on at this level you are either a)farming greens, b)trying to channel a new pet, c)about to die, or d)you just overnuked and are hoping for someone to taunt or mez the beasty. In any of those cases the DS isn't going to do much for you.<br>
INT: If your INT is really lacking, this may actually be atractive to you - until you look at the costs.<br>
Effective Casting Level : all this effect actually does is reduce fizzle rates. Do you find yourself fizzling to an extreme extent?<br>
<br>
Compare the desirable part of this (the INT) to what you get for the same number of points spent directly on INT.<br>
Level 1 : 10 Int 50% of the time vs 6 Int 100% of the time<br>
Level 2 : 15 Int 50% of the time vs 18 Int 100% of the time (admitedly you have to be spending in PoP abilities to get this)<br>
Level 3 : 20 Int 50% of the time vs 30 Int 100% of the time and 3 AA points left over since you maxed out the INT AAs (both General and PoP).<br>
<br>
If you really need +50 INT from AAs (30 from direct INT purchases and +20 from FIRE 3), you need to start thinking about replacing that full suit of Raw Silk you are wearing.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Water</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Enduring Breath<br>
5 STA regen<br>
+1/2/4 mana/tick<br>
<br>
EB: We have waterstones. You can also get EB items rather easily by the time you are 59+. Doesn't really help with anything.<br>
Sta regen: Nearly pointless.<br>
Mana Regen : Admitedly mana regen is nice. The problem here is the mana regen relative to the point cost.<br>
<br>
If you manage to keep the water form for its full 36 minutes out of 72, you average 0.5/1.0/2.0 mana/tick over those 72 minutes for total point costs of 3/9/18.<br>
That works out to regen/aa point of  0.166 / 0.111 / 0.111<br>
Compared that to Mental Clarity (1/2/3 for 2/6/12 AAs total) with its regens of 0.5 / 0.333 / 0.25<br>
<br>
Most people agree that MC1 is worth it, MC 2 is OK, and MC 3 is overpriced. Compared to Water Elemental Form (any level) the overpriced MC 3 is a bargain, giving between 50% (compared to Water 1) and 125% (compared to Water 2 or 3)more mana/aa point. <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:medium;">Zyphyr Runnersbane</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
